唯獨美國升緊  有乜理據唔選侵  到底 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-24T06:02:10.000Z","msg":"今日哩篇野有參考價值<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\nI don&rsquo;t believe they really want socialism. Few even understand what it is. What they want is change. They see little hope for improvement in their situations, no matter how hard they work and sacrifice. They don&rsquo;t see anyone in authority trying to help them. So, when someone offers what sound like easy answers, they jump aboard. As Harvard professor Ed Glaeser says (my paraphrase), people think of socialism as &ldquo;hyperredistribution.&rdquo; They are not looking to control the means of production per se, just redistributing the fruits of that production.<br />\n<br />\nIn one regard, Sanders is similar to Trump in 2016&mdash;an outsider whose message activates previously neglected voters. Trump went on to win. If Sanders gets the nomination, it&rsquo;s easy to imagine scenarios where he wins, too.<br />\n<br />\nThat the US could plausibly swing from someone like Trump to someone like Sanders in the space of four years says, to me at least, that something bigger is happening. Until we fix it, desperate people will keep making desperate choices.<br />\n<br />\n⋯⋯⋯I see two answers to that. One is in the question itself. Your financial condition can be better than it was but still not where you think it should be. If you are no longer drowning and are instead treading water with no lifeboat in sight, then yes, your condition has &ldquo;improved.&rdquo; But you&rsquo;re still looking for answers.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.mauldineconomics.com/frontlinethoughts/why-americans-want-socialism\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mauldineconomics.com%2Ffrontlinethoughts%2Fwhy-americans-want-socialism&d=SulGM1C%2FSMvfI9hDp2hpAm6H7LaHGbUBdoVXdg05ZHE%3D&h=5ea77b99\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.mauldineconomics.com/frontlinethoughts/why-americans-want-socialism</a>"},{"pid":"7000988849c9dde89a27c21fa79002ae879e8c64","tid":1894700,"uid":228143,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"5f3a5ed4dc505e23816b3553db09a14149ef2257","tid":1894700,"uid":89517,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"1e6acfe6fadf6b4f097644995fcc50cf81259fec","tid":1894700,"uid":228143,"like":2,"dislike":1,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-24T05:56:40.000Z","msg":"蕭生19都話連任機會好大<br />\n<br />\n冇得輸"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-24T05:58:04.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-24T06:02:13.000Z","msg":"強強聯手世紀大和解呀<br />\n今次冇包咬頸<br />\n上次台選笑到仆街<br />\n一個話大勝一個話險勝"},{"pid":"f688b32a4c38320a41842e637fecbb014bc8e351","tid":1894700,"uid":103916,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"9fe5d66c53928d141cfd580f19323c2aab84a956","tid":1894700,"uid":124983,"like":6,"dislike":2,"score":4,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-02-24T05:46:35.000Z","msg":"關7婆咩事"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-24T06:14:50.000Z","msg":"7婆，剋中共。"},{"pid":"fa65016fb2c852f033c3115be5503c16ec2a2047","tid":1894700,"uid":242605,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-24T06:14:57.000Z","msg":"開咗新Post 幫手推<br />\n[YouTube 戰線] 抖咗咁耐係時候做翻啲嘢！同我入嚟睇晒佢！<br />\n<a href=\"https://lih.kg/1894731\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://lih.kg/1894731</a><br />\n- 分享自 LIHKG 討論區"}]}